Note: this attack works anywhere.

Please, a phone call, or in-person meeting would be good.

You can:

* slack
* twitter dm
* phone

You have all of these contact methods.

There is little more I can do here and we are rolling out a fix, but I want
to be extremely clear that the attack is composed of MANY distinct pieces:

1) banana king (reported for over a year)
2) client spamming
3) block sizes too large
4) mempool issues causing echoes / amplification
5) gas issues overall
6) lack of field length limits in ibc for reciever in send transactions
7) lack of field length limits in ibc memos
8) p2p issues of an unknown type, could be a lack of throttling or back
pressure
9) consensus issues resulting in an invalid proposer signature error
10) invalid block parts error
11) ability to dos through globalfee whitelists, even with a 1mb block size

Thus it is my opinion that we should eliminate the globalfee whitelist on
the cosmos hub.

But there is a ton of other work to be done, too.

Ultimately, the fix:

https://forum.cosmos.network/t/reduce-maximum-block-size-to-1mb/11615

was contributed by Assaf Morami



